<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
Nomenclatural notes: In the original description, the species was described based on “ 
<specimenCount box="[1186,1211,153,179]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<specimenCount box="[1210,1227,153,179]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
” collected on “ 
<date pageId="5" pageNumber="150" value="1893-07-15">15 Juillet 1893</date>
”. Two specimens have been found in 
<collectionCode box="[718,775,189,215]" country="Russia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/vmfx-g997" name="Zoological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">ZISP</collectionCode>
but both are females (cabinet 217/drawer 6). One of them was designated a 
<typeStatus box="[345,448,225,251]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">lectotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Laszlo, G. M. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Ronkay, L. &amp; Witt, T." box="[488,761,225,251]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" pagination="1 - 683" refId="ref6734" refString="Laszlo, G. M., Ronkay, G., Ronkay, L. &amp; Witt, T. (2007) The Thyatiridae of Eurasia Including the Sundaland and New Guinea (Lepidoptera). Esperiana, 13, 1 - 683." type="journal article" year="2007">
László 
<emphasis box="[568,625,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">&amp; al.</emphasis>
(2007: 178)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="Alph. The" authorityName="Alph. The" box="[797,1145,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Psidopala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opalesens">
<emphasis box="[797,1026,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Psidopala opalesens</emphasis>
Alph. The
</taxonomicName>
second female is supplied with an additional red rectangular label: « 
<typeStatus box="[629,784,261,287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Paralectotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[793,814,261,287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
| 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1897" box="[837,1066,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Thyatira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opalescens">
<emphasis box="[837,1066,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Thyatira opalescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
| 
<bibRefCitation author="Alpheraky, S." box="[1079,1267,261,287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" pagination="83 - 149" refId="ref6399" refString="Alpheraky, S. (1897) Lepidopteresdes provinces chinoises Se-Tchouen et Kham recueillis, en 1893, par M-r G. N. Potanine. Memoires sur les Lepidopteres, 9, 83 - 149." type="journal article" year="1897">Alphéraky, 1897</bibRefCitation>
| Design. 
<collectionCode box="[1385,1407,261,287]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
.G. Mironov | et 
<collectionCode box="[295,315,297,323]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode box="[319,339,297,323]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. Zolotuhin, 2019”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
Only two females are present and no male. It is possible that S. Alphéraky had wrongly interpreted gender in one specimen or that the 
<typeStatus box="[432,480,369,395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">type</typeStatus>
series included more than these 
<specimenCount box="[846,987,369,395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="generic">2 specimens</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
